# 6. Benefits of DevOps

- Faster software delivery
- Better collaboration
- Automated testing
- Continuous deployment
- Improved software quality
- Reduced manual effort
- Faster issue resolution

---

# 7. Challenges of DevOps

- Initial setup takes time
- Learning curve for tools
- Infrastructure cost
- Continuous monitoring required

---

# 8. Real-Time Example

A developer fixes a bug in an online shopping application.

1. The code is pushed to GitHub.
2. Jenkins automatically builds the project.
3. Automated tests are executed.
4. Docker creates the application image.
5. The application is deployed to the server.
6. Monitoring tools continuously check the application's health.

